webpackJsonp([0xe6483971b4df],{672:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<blockquote>\n<p>This page is a work in progress.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h1 id="what-is-graphql"><a href="#what-is-graphql" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>What is GraphQL?</h1>\n<p>graphql.org describes it as “…a query language for APIs and a runtime for\nfulfilling those queries with your existing data”.</p>\n<p>Gatsby uses GraphQL to create a consistent interface between your static site\nand your data sources, where data sources can be anything from local markdown\nfiles to a remote API.</p>\n<p>Gatsby describes your data by creating GraphQL <em>schemas</em> from your data sources.</p>\n<p>GraphQL <em>queries</em> can then be associated with your Gatsby pages, ensuring each\npage receives exactly the data it needs.</p>\n<h1 id="why-graphql"><a href="#why-graphql" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Why GraphQL?</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>As Gatsby runs on both server (at build time) &#x26; client, need way to specify\nwhich data is needed.</li>\n<li>This is a <em>build-time only</em> use of GraphQL. You don’t need to run a GraphQL\nserver in production.</li>\n<li>Convenient way to describe data requirements of component.</li>\n<li>Why query colocation rocks</li>\n<li>Uses the Relay Modern compiler behind the scenes</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id="basic-terminology"><a href="#basic-terminology" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Basic Terminology</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Types based on file type + way data can be transformed</li>\n<li>Connections</li>\n<li>Shallow intro to how data layer works e.g. source and transformer plugins.</li>\n<li>Compare to webpack loaders — like loaders except create schema that can then\nbe queried.</li>\n<li>Named queries?</li>\n<li>Using query parameters to manipulate results?</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id="example-queries"><a href="#example-queries" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Example queries</h1>\n<p>Showing off sorting, filtering, picking fields, programmatic transformations</p>\n<p><a href="https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/52e36b9994a86fc473cd2f966ab6b6f87ee8eedb/packages/gatsby/src/schema/__tests__/infer-graphql-input-type-test.js#L116-L432">Some example queries from Gatsby’s tests</a> -\nlook for `template literal blocks` with <code>allNode{}</code> in them.</p>\n<p>…</p>\n<h1 id="further-reading"><a href="#further-reading" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Further reading</h1>\n<h2 id="getting-started-with-graphql"><a href="#getting-started-with-graphql" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Getting started with GraphQL</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://graphql.org/learn/">http://graphql.org/learn/</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://services.github.com/on-demand/graphql/">https://services.github.com/on-demand/graphql/</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://apis.guru/graphql-voyager/">https://apis.guru/graphql-voyager/</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.howtographql.com/">https://www.howtographql.com/</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://reactjs.org/blog/2015/05/01/graphql-introduction.html">https://reactjs.org/blog/2015/05/01/graphql-introduction.html</a></li>\n<li>…</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id="advanced-readings-on-graphql"><a href="#advanced-readings-on-graphql" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Advanced readings on GraphQL</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://facebook.github.io/graphql/October2016/">GraphQL specification</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://medium.com/the-graphqlhub/graphql-tour-interfaces-and-unions-7dd5be35de0d">Interfaces and Unions</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://facebook.github.io/relay/docs/en/compiler-architecture.html">Gatsby uses the Relay Compiler</a></li>\n<li>…</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id="todo--create-live-graphql-explorer-for-gatsbyjsorg"><a href="#todo--create-live-graphql-explorer-for-gatsbyjsorg" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>TODO — create live GraphQL explorer for GatsbyJS.org</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>iFrame of graphiql instance for this site running on Heroku so people can run\nlive queries.</li>\n</ul>',excerpt:"This page is a work in progress. What is GraphQL? graphql.org describes it as “…a query language for APIs and a runtime for\nfulfilling those…",timeToRead:2,frontmatter:{title:"Querying with GraphQL"},parent:{__typename:"File",relativePath:"docs/querying-with-graphql.md"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/docs/querying-with-graphql/"}}}});
